{
  "info": {
    "name": "YoUnion — Supabase PostgREST",
    "description": "Read-focused collection for inspecting YoUnion database tables via Supabase's auto-generated PostgREST API.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import `younion.postman_environment.json` alongside this collection.\n2. Set `supabase_url` (e.g. `http://127.0.0.1:54321` for local, your project URL for hosted).\n3. Set `supabase_key` to your **publishable** key (`SUPABASE_KEY` in `.env`). This grants anon access — RLS-protected tables (users, user_profiles, user_cost_of_living) will return `[]` until you call **Auth → Sign in with password**, which captures a user JWT into `{{user_jwt}}` for you.\n4. Open any folder and hit Send.\n\n## Headers\n- `apikey`: identifies the project. Always the publishable key.\n- `Authorization: Bearer ...`: anon access if it's the publishable key, authenticated access if it's a user JWT.\n\nThe collection-level `Authorization` defaults to `{{supabase_key}}` so anon-readable tables Just Work. To switch to authenticated mode, change a request's auth to `Bearer {{user_jwt}}` (or override at the folder level).\n\n## Query DSL cheatsheet (PostgREST)\n- `?select=col1,col2` — projection\n- `?col=eq.value` — equality (`gt`, `lt`, `gte`, `lte`, `neq`, `like`, `ilike`, `in.(a,b)`, `is.null`)\n- `?order=col.desc.nullslast`\n- `?limit=25&offset=50`\n- `?select=*,related_table(*)` — embed FK relations\n- Header `Prefer: count=exact` — total row count in `Content-Range` response header\n- Header `Accept: application/vnd.pgrst.object+json` — return single object instead of array (404 if 0 or >1 rows)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{supabase_key}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "rest_path", "value": "/rest/v1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "auth_path", "value": "/auth/v1", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Get a user JWT to access RLS-protected tables. The 'Sign in with password' request automatically writes the returned access_token into `{{user_jwt}}` via a test script.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Sign in with password",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('user_jwt', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('user_id', json.user && json.user.id);",
                  "  console.log('Saved user_jwt and user_id to environment');",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.warn('No access_token in response', json);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{supabase_key}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{user_password}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{supabase_url}}{{auth_path}}/token?grant_type=password",
              "host": ["{{supabase_url}}{{auth_path}}"],
              "path": ["token"],
              "query": [{ "key": "grant_type", "value": "password" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get current user (using user_jwt)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{user_jwt}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "apikey", "value": "{{supabase_key}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{supabase_url}}{{auth_path}}/user",
              "host": ["{{supabase_url}}{{auth_path}}"],
              "path": ["user"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
